<item>
 <title>The Flavors of SVG</title>
 <link>https://dev-2015drupalcampcoloradoorg.pantheonsite.io/session/flavors-svg</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-session-timeslot field-type-entityreference field-label-inline clearfix&quot;&gt;&lt;div &gt;Timeslot:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div &gt;&lt;div &gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/content/june-20th-day-1&quot;&gt;June 20th - Day 1 16:00-16:45&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-session-room field-type-entityreference field-label-inline clearfix&quot;&gt;&lt;div &gt;Room:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div &gt;&lt;div &gt;Concert Hall&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div &gt;&lt;div  property=&quot;content:encoded&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;There is so much more to Scalable Vector Graphics (SVG) than resolution independence. Unlike a static bitmap, SVG can be animated; styled with CSS; even generated dynamically from Drupal content.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this session we&#039;ll look at some of the more interesting applications of SVG. We&#039;ll focus on the different ways of implementing SVG on your Drupal site; the pros and cons of each and why you might choose one approach over another.  Using modern tools and practical examples, this session is intended to inspire both designers and developers to make more dynamic interfaces with SVG.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;iframe width=&quot;560&quot; height=&quot;315&quot; src=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/embed/doCeHcyIxz8&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot; allowfullscreen=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-speaker field-type-entityreference field-label-inline clearfix&quot;&gt;&lt;div &gt;Speaker(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div &gt;&lt;div &gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/pixelwhip&quot;&gt;pixelwhip&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-track field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-inline clearfix&quot;&gt;&lt;div &gt;Track:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div &gt;&lt;div &gt;Front End&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
